The paper introduces a novel evolutionary algorithm that uses semantic networks and commonsense reasoning to preserve the meaningfulness of the networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a fitness measure that is computed through structure mapping, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the open-ended generation of networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
